The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, June 6: Japan International Co-operation Agency will start preparing a feasibility report this month on the proposed bridge over the Hooghly connecting Raichak in South 24-Parganas with Kukrahati in East Midnapore.

 A team from the Japanese governments consulting agency met the chief minister today and sought administrative support for the study. The agency will take about 18 months to submit the final report.

Calcutta: A man in his mid-30s was held on Tuesday after 

he threatened his friend saying he will kidnap his five-year-old son and kill 

him if Rs 4 lakh was not paid. Police said Bedford Fernandes, who was involved 

in a brawl during a dinner at his friends Kasba house, made the threat over 

the phone.

Chinsurah: Two motorcyclists were killed in Chanditala, Hooghly, 

20 km from Calcutta, on Tuesday. A bus hit them.




